You are building a Next.js 15 fullstack app with App Router, Prisma, Auth.js, and Tailwind.

ALWAYS:
- Use Server Components by default — add "use client" only when needed
- Validate input in Server Actions with Zod before any database operation
- Map Prisma models to DTOs before sending to client components
- Use `revalidatePath()` after mutations that affect cached pages
- Prefetch data at the server level when possible (generateMetadata, layout.tsx)
- Add proper error handling to all Server Actions — return errors, don't throw

NEVER:
- Fetch the same data in both server and client components
- Expose Prisma models or sensitive fields to the client
- Trust client-side validation alone — always re-validate on server
- Use `router.refresh()` as a substitute for proper revalidation
- Skip auth checks in Server Actions just because the page is protected
- Use `$queryRaw` with user input — SQL injection risk
